			<name>
				<baseName xml:lang="en">Recycled Polypropylene Granules</baseName>
				<baseName xml:lang="zh">再生聚丙烯颗粒</baseName>
			</name>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="en">Polypropylene pellets; PP granules</common:synonyms>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="zh">Polypropylene pellets; PP granules</common:synonyms>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification name="ILCD 1.1" classes="../ILCDClassification.xml">
					<common:class level="0">Materials production</common:class>
					<common:class level="1">Plastics</common:class>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Recycled polypropylene granules are produced through a process of cleaning and washing plastic waste, cutting it into small pieces, and melting it in an extruder. The granule lump is then sliced and glued together to form pellets. These pellets are ready to be used by manufacturers after the polypropylene recycling process, which includes separating PP from mixtures with other plastics and contaminants. Recycling plastic into pellets is an effective way of reducing waste and helping to save the environment.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">再生聚丙烯颗粒的生产工艺是：清洗塑料废料，将其切成小块，然后在挤出机中熔化。然后将颗粒块切片并粘合在一起，形成颗粒。聚丙烯回收过程包括将聚丙烯从与其他塑料和杂质的混合物中分离出来。将塑料回收成颗粒是减少废物和保护环境的有效方法。</common:generalComment>
